By changing line 205 in Engine.cpp from
    String resourcePrefixPath = GetParameter(parameters, "ResourcePrefixPath", defaultPrefixPath).GetString();

to
    String resourcePrefixPath = AddTrailingSlash(GetParameter(parameters, "ResourcePrefixPath", defaultPrefixPath).GetString());

Does this make sense? May be a non-issue, but it bothered me for almost 30 minutes when I wasn't able to set the prefix path. Finally I gave up and checked the sources. This is bread and butter code, should the user really have to worry about a trailing slash or not when it's so easy for the API to do it in a portable way?
